1. VPC Networking
Design and configure a Custom Mode VPC by creating subnets in us-central1 and asia-
east1 regions to support multi- region networking. (3)
Activity 3: Essential Google Cloud Infrastructure: Foundation
Lab: VPC Networking

✅ Task 1: Create Custom Mode VPC (Multi-Region)
Step 1: Open VPC Network
Go to Google Cloud Console
Navigate → VPC network → VPC networks
Click Create VPC Network
Step 2: Configure VPC
Name: custom-vpc
Subnet mode: ✅ Custom
Step 3: Create Subnet (Region 1 – us-central1)
Click Add Subnet
Name: subnet-us
Region: us-central1
IP range: 10.0.1.0/24
Click Done
Step 4: Create Subnet (Region 2 – asia-east1)
Click Add Subnet
Name: subnet-asia
Region: asia-east1
IP range: 10.0.2.0/24
Click Done
Step 5: Create VPC
Click Create

✔️ Now your Custom Mode VPC with multi-region subnets is ready.

✅ Task 2: Create Firewall Rule
Step 6: Go to Firewall
Navigate → VPC network → Firewall
Click Create Firewall Rule
Step 7: Configure Rule
Name: allow-ssh-icmp
Network: custom-vpc
Direction: Ingress
Action: Allow
Targets: All instances
Source IP: 0.0.0.0/0
Protocols:
✔️ tcp:22 (SSH)
✔️ icmp (Ping)

Click Create

✅ Task 3: Create VM Instances in Different Regions
Step 8: Create VM in us-central1
Go to Compute Engine → VM instances
Click Create Instance

Configuration:

Name: vm-us
Region: us-central1
Zone: us-central1-a
Machine type: e2-micro
OS: Debian 12

👉 Networking:

Network: custom-vpc
Subnet: subnet-us

Click Create

Step 9: Create VM in asia-east1

Repeat steps:

Configuration:

Name: vm-asia
Region: asia-east1
Zone: asia-east1-a

👉 Networking:

Network: custom-vpc
Subnet: subnet-asia

Click Create

✅ Task 4: Test Connectivity
Step 10: SSH into VM

Open Cloud Shell and run:

gcloud compute ssh vm-us --zone=us-central1-a
Step 11: Ping Other VM (Internal IP)

Inside VM:

ping -c 3 <vm-asia-internal-ip>

✔️ You should get successful response

✅ Expected Result
VPC created in Custom mode
Subnets in:
us-central1
asia-east1
2 VMs created in different regions
Internal communication works (ping success)
🎯 Key Concepts (Important for Exam)
Custom Mode VPC: Full control over subnets
Multi-region networking: Same VPC across regions
Internal IP communication works across regions
Firewall rules required for access
